ge of the cliff where the portal to Elven city.<br>
<br>
Monsters of terror and shadows creep like wraiths shrilling about and creating confusion.  In their wake where their feet stepped the ground turns and the life dies.  Leading the horde floats a thin figure dressed in a long dark green cloak.<br>
<br>
The man is young, no more then twenty years of age.  His blonde hair is kept with it being combed back, save, for his bains that hang in front of his forehead.  He has a small goatee that emphasizes the contours of his chin.  A thick black belt rests on his hips contrasting against his robe.  Be all appearances this man does not belong here.<br>
<br>
“Open your doors Elves!”<br>
<br>
The man waits but a few seconds.<br>
<br>
“Ha!  Have it your way!”<br>
<br>
From the raised hands comes a soft glow.  The contours of the young mans hands light up and the air is pierced with the sound of shrills.  Then, with a ground-shaking boom, that much like of thunder, the Elven city fades into view.  As the city comes into sights the hordes with gleaming eyes flaring like fire spill down.<br>
<br>
The man floats down into the chaos, fire quickly filling the air, the smell of burning flesh lingers across the nose.  In minutes the city has fallen.  However, one building stands.  Bright white and stalwart the shadows ravaging the city seem to being ignoring this structure.<br>
<br>
The man descends to the bridge below him that leads to the defiant structure.  He comes to a rest to where just his toes barely skim the ground.  He glides to the door and places his right hand on it.<br>
<br>
“Come out!”<br>
<br>
Then promptly the door caves in.  The man floats in and before him a crowd of cowering elves and around them a ring of guards.  As the man approaches the King of the Elves speaks.<br>
<br>
“Sonto . . . Validus’s brightness pupil.  You are truly your mentor’s prodigy.  Why do you come and disturb my city?”<br>
<br>
In a flash Sonto glides through the crowd of the last of the city.  In his wake a distorted wave of air passes over the crowd.  As the wave washes over the crowd they are torn apart.  As Sonto sets down to ground to meet the King on equal grounds the bodies fall in pieces.  Sonto stands looking up to the King, the elf is much taller then him.  Oddly, Sonto’s breaths are labored and sweat trickles down his brows.<br>
<br>
Gallad speaks holding back tears; “You over exert yourself in this senseless act.  I knew you when you were young, you could break free any time you want.”<br>
<br>
Sonto reacts violently grabbing a hold of Gallad’s neck and rising into the air bringing Galad with him by the neck.<br>
<br>
“Shut up!  Tell me where they are!”<br>
<br>
Through a tight throat, “Whom do you speak of?”<br>
<br>
“I am giving you one chance to save your own life.  Tell me where they are.  I know they were here.”<br>
<br>
“You know I can’t tell you that.  Tell Validus for me that he needs to learn how to control his anger.”<br>
<br>
Sonto floats in the air with Gallad beneath him dangling by the neck.  His hands tighten, though his fingers shake.  With a tear rolling down his cheek Gallad’s neck snaps.<br>
<br>
“You should have told me.”<br>
<br>
Sonto drops the body of the king and promptly exits the room with haste.  A large orc who is dressed in dark serrated armor comes to greet Sonto.<br>
<br>
“Agaolite take your men and go through the valley, kill any humans and elves you see along the way.  Order the wraiths to go through the river pass and remove it of any human and elf life.  I’ll go forward alone.” <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugrandxduke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GrandxDuke</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/3/02 1:34:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugothicchaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gothic chaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/1/02 11:35:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Flight</span><hr size=1> As the company rode onwards without delay, Caprice's horse reared up and flung her to the ground. She tumbled to a halt, and sat for a moment, a dazed look on her face. Her horse began dancing about, rearing his head and motioning off to the direction form which they had just come.<br>
<br>
Caprice stood up, dusting off the dirt and took her horse by the bridal.<br>
&quot;What in Heaven's name were you doing?&quot; The horse neighed and kicked, his eyes wide. He kept pullling towards the direction of the elven city.<br>
&quot;Oh fine, I'll look,&quot;She turned slowly, mumbling curses when he felt silent.<br>
<br>
A great pillar of smoke rose out of the place of the elven city. Akume turned his eyes away from the sight only to see that a horde of creatures coming in there direction.<br>
&quot;We must hurry!&quot;Akume shouted. <br>
Caprice mounted and the rode off, faster than before, one of the two elves in their party looking back occasionaly. <br>
<br>
