<br>
Elil pressed his heels hard into the sides of his warhorse to keep pace with Anlore.  &quot;You take everyone to those caves.  I'll fall back, leave some traps and lead them in the wrong direction.  I think I know where you're headed, I'll see you there!&quot;  <br>
<br>
He turned and was out of site before the others even noticed.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=psychosoldier>Psycho Soldier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/3/02 2:11:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=71>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Flight</span><hr size=1> Agaolite dawned his enveloping shroud, &quot;Mount your steeds!!&quot; he shouted with all the fury of destruction brewing in his veins.  &quot;Tonight we ride, tomorrow we live!!,&quot; with this he mounted his night mare and took to the torched road way.  The only good life is the one of taking life.<br>
<br>
His black charred shroud masked and warped his already immense stature, furthering his intimidating figure.  All that could be seen was the one good eye, crimson in color, left to him by his father.  His armor turned and clattered alerting any living soul to his coming presence, his foul breath would let you know what he was, and his zambato would let you know your death was coming to greet you.<br>
<br>
No such god for sakeing, bastard child could have been spawned off of the serene nature of mother earth.  No, this warped, perverted monstrosity was forged from the wicked efforts of man.<br>
<br>
Monsters have said to have many faces in past tales, but this creature has only one, but even still it's hard to say exactly what that face is, seeing that few have had the unfortunate luck of seeing and fewer more to survive without some sort of prolonged scar crippling them for the rest of their days.<br>
<br>
Nightmares come and go, but this one has yet to make his leave, god help those who find their journeys end in front of this Orc.<br>
