<br>
&quot;They make my job too easy!&quot; cried Agaolite in his booming voice.  &quot;This trail leads straight out of the forest and onto the plains!&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;Then that's where we ride?&quot; questioned his second in command.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Fool!  What battle seasoned warior would be stupid enough to head to flat land when pursued by an ary on horseback?  No, someone may be trying to lead us a stray.&quot;  He then paused for a moment staring into the high mountains.  &quot;Take three forths of the men into the plains and find whoever did this, I will take the rest of the men to the best hiding place in this whole forest.&quot;  <br>
