<br>
Turning around –<br>
<br>
“Agaolite!”<br>
<br>
Agaolite pays no attention and continues his march through the forest.  Sonto glides over and rises a few feet in the air so he can comfortably place his right hand on Agalite’s shoulder.  Promptly Agoalite turns around and roars in fury.<br>
<br>
With a stern response that eerily echoes throughout the forest –<br>
<br>
“CALM!”<br>
<br>
Like a switch the blood rage Orc calms and takes a calmer demeanor.<br>
<br>
“What are you doing here?  You are supposed to be in the valley.”<br>
<br>
“Horde small ‘cause others ordered to kill in valley passage.  I here to kill.  The interlopers here so I kill them.”<br>
<br>
“Your vocabulary is improving.”<br>
<br>
Sonto looks about for a few seconds as he takes in the land.  There are caves up ahead and further from there are dwarvern catacombs.  Then something catches Sonto’s sense, something magical, that gleams with an explosive radiance.  Most likely a trap –<br>
<br>
“Go through the forest and don’t look back.  They are up ahead and you will have to hurry if you want to catch them and become Validus’s most prized.”<br>
<br>
Turning and charging Agaolite does not take a second to think about the proposed prospect.  Becoming Validus’s most liked is an urge that it cannot refuse.  Sonto falls back down to the ground a few inches before his toes touch.  He then zooms to the east and begins making a huge circle at great speed around where he sent Agaolite.<br>
<br>
“Dumb orc won’t survive this one.  If he does make it through the traps he can kill who ever set those.  The caves are where they are.  Validus over stated their potential, a little obvious of them.”<br>
