<br>
Those traps were for real, but no matter.  As long as Agaolite had men to dispose of, this would be a minor detour.<br>
<br>
With a defining roar of might from Agaolite all the orc that were about, sixty in all <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (you must understand sixty orc's is a very big number when it comes to matters related to orc's)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> took to their fastest of feet and leapt forward.<br>
<br>
Agaolite stood proud and not the least effected as one by one his orc comrades fell to sounders.  Yes, this truly was a skilled opponent, Agaolite knew he'd find himself having the pleasure of devouring this morsel of an opponent soon.<br>
<br>
Now taking a slow march Agaolite kept his eye at the best of a scan it could muster.  Who ever had wiped out his entire army could not be far away.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (As a note: amongst orc kind it does no matter the circumstances (such as ordering all orc dead) who ever actually did the killing was required to pay for the act)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
An odd clearing began to show itself.  Agaolite froze when he came to this strange marvel, up to this point the entire forest had been thick and rich with growth.  For it to drop like this did not make sense.  There was a point, there was a point, there had to be.<br>
<br>
Now pondering, Agaolite looked about with his one good eye.  As good as the eye could it saw nothing of vague importance.  Of course though, not all dangers can be seen with a eye.  There was more a foot here.<br>
<br>
Being a Orc of action, Agaolite entered the clearing step by step, listening, waiting, stepping again then waiting again.  Agaolite kept with the careful approach until the center of the clearing came to rest under his feet.  The bristles of hair on the nape of the back side of his head stood as straight as lumber.<br>
<br>
He felt this before... something approaching... trying to out wit him. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (Much like his father did when he took his right eye)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
